text.div:
klinicapifhir

The official URL for this implementation guide is: 

https://digitalware-klinic.github.io/fhir/indisa/ImplementationGuide/fhir.digital-ware.klinic-api-fhir

FHIR implementation guide for Klinic API FHIR (Klinic-HIS) interoperability scenarios, edited by DigitalWare S.A.

name: klinicapifhir
title: Klinic API FHIR Implementation Guide: IG Release 1 - Digital Ware S.A.
description: FHIR implementation guide for Klinic API FHIR (Klinic-HIS) interoperability scenarios, edited by DigitalWare S.A.

resource.name: Account
resource.description: Patient account, where all charges made at the outpatient or hospital level are found.

resource.name: Appointment
resource.description: Registered appointments of the patient for each general and specialized medical consultation and the performance of laboratory and imaging tests, among others.

resource.name: Appointment Response
resource.description: Response regarding the scheduling of the patient's appointment according to the availability of the agenda or regarding cancellations, reviews, among other activities on each appointment.

resource.name: Document Electronic
resource.description: Electronic composition document that allows the exchange of information between processes or between integration points and that has to do with the patient's medical information.

resource.name: Condition
resource.description: A clinical condition, problem, diagnosis, or other event, situation, issue, or clinical concept that has risen to a level of concern.

resource.name: Coverage patient
resource.description: Patient's health coverage policy.

resource.name: Device
resource.description: A type of a manufactured item that is used in the provision of healthcare without being substantially changed through that activity.

resource.name: Diagnostic report for laboratory, imamging study and cardiovascular tests
resource.description: Clinical diagnostic reports of the patient (laboratory, imamging study and cardiovascular tests).

resource.name: Endpoint
resource.description: Contact points where the exchange, update and consultation of medical information of the patient is allowed.

resource.name: Healthcare Service
resource.description: health services that are provided to the patient, once they enter the provider's facilities.

resource.name: Imaging Study
resource.description: A set of images produced in single study at patient.

resource.name: Device
resource.description:
FHIR resource profile for Active Implantable Medical Devices (AIMD), invasive medical devices, custom medical devices, and invasive or reusable surgical medical devices.

Many of these devices are partially or completely absorbed.

Such as: pacemaker, extends, catheter, IUD, and surgical instruments.

resource.name: Location Area
resource.description: Physical location of each of the clinical and administrative areas within a building: Floor, Area, Wing, Waiting room, intensive care unit, among others.

resource.name: Location Bed
resource.description: Physical location of each of the clinical areas within a building:  Bed.

resource.name: Location Building
resource.description: Physical location of each of the clinical and administrative areas within a building:  Building, Wing of building, Tower, etc.

resource.name: Location Functional Unit
resource.description: Physical location of each of the clinical and administrative areas within a building:  Functional Unit.

resource.name: Location Room
resource.description: Physical location of each of the clinical and administrative areas within a building:  Room, Consulting room, etc.

resource.name: Medication Administration
resource.description: Describes the event of a patient consuming or otherwise being administered a medication.

resource.name: Medication dispense
resource.description: Indicates that a medication product is to be or has been dispensed for a named person/patient. This includes a description of the medication product (supply) provided and the instructions for administering the medication. The medication dispense is the result of a pharmacy system responding to a medication order.

resource.name: Medication
resource.description: Identification and definition of a medication for the purposes of prescribing, dispensing, and administering a medication as well as for making statements about medication use.

resource.name: Medication Request
resource.description: An order or request for both supply of the medication and the instructions for administration of the medication to a patient.

resource.name: Message header
resource.description: Message header in the messaging exchange.

resource.name: Observation
resource.description: Observation laboratory and imaging.

resource.name: Organization Healthcare Provider
resource.description: Organization Healthcare Provider.

resource.name: Patient
resource.description: Data of patient.

resource.name: Practitioner
resource.description: Practitioner of healht.

resource.name: Practitioner Role
resource.description: Role of practitioner.

resource.name: Procedure
resource.description: Medical procedures in health.

resource.name: Questionnaire response
resource.description: Questionnaire responses

resource.name: Questionnaire
resource.description: Questionnaire of Survey

resource.name: Schedule patient
resource.description: Schedule patient.

resource.name: Service Request
resource.description: Medical order for health services.

resource.name: Slot
resource.description: Agenda spaces available for appointment assignments.

resource.name: Specimen
resource.description: A sample to be used for analysis.

resource.name: Account Amount
resource.description: Amount of the account, which totals the services provided to the patient,

resource.name: Admit telemedicine
resource.description: Active agenda for telemedicine care.

resource.name: BedWithOxygen
resource.description: Indicator if a bed has oxygen or not

resource.name: Birth Place

resource.name: Bonus Amount
resource.description: Amount of the bonus that legalizes the payment of the patient's account, totally or partially.

resource.name: Fecha/Hora cancelacion cita
resource.description: Cate and time of cancellation of the appointment.

resource.name: Sancion cancelacion cita
resource.description: Penalty for cancellation of appointment.

resource.description: Census bed indicator

resource.name: ChargeBed
resource.description: Indicator if a bed was charged or not

resource.name: Clinical discharge type
resource.description: Types of clinical discharge of the patient, at the hospitalization and emergency level.

resource.name: Consultations Amount
resource.description: Amount of consultations or health benefits, made to the patient.

resource.name: Copayment Amount
resource.description: Amount of the copayment to be paid by the patient or their person in charge, if a value is pending after paying off their account against the value of the bond from their insurer.

resource.name: Cultural group
resource.description: Cultural group to which the patient belongs.

resource.description: Disability of the patient.

resource.name: Education level
resource.description: Patient education level.

resource.description: Patient's first surname.

resource.name: Gender patient

resource.description: Hours of attention of the schedule.

resource.description: Place of issuance of patient identification.

resource.name: Medical Fees
resource.description: Medical fees that are charged to the patient's account, once the corresponding medical consultations have been made.

resource.name: Medication Amount
resource.description: Amount of medication given to the patient and charged to his account.

resource.name: Second surname patient
resource.description: Second surname of the patient.

resource.name: MultipleOccupation
resource.description: Describes whether a location admits multiple patients or professionals

resource.name: Nationality patient
resource.description: Nationality of the patient.

resource.name: Newborn
resource.description: Extension that allows registering whether or not the patient is a newborn.

resource.description: Patient occupation.

resource.description: Population group to which the patient belongs.

resource.name: Patient identification
resource.description: Patient identification.

resource.name: Quota Patient
resource.description: Number of patients admitted in the agenda.

resource.name: Rate modality
resource.description: Rate mode on the services provided to the patient, according to their stay in the facilities where health services are provided.

resource.name: Regional location identifier
resource.description: Identification of the regional location of residence of the patient.

resource.name: Religion
resource.description: Religion patient.

resource.name: Subservices
resource.description: Subservices on health services.

resource.name: Supplies Amount
resource.description: Amount of supplies charged to the patient's account, according to the medical benefits performed.

resource.name: VirtualBed
resource.description: Indicator if a bed is virtual or not.

resource.name: CoveragesTypeCl
resource.description: This is a coding system that contains the types of health coverage applicable to the Chilean jurisdiction.

resource.name: ISAPRES
resource.description: This is a coding system that contains the insurance organizations classified in ISAPRES..

resource.description: This is a coding system that contains the rate modality codes for the interoperability scenario of INDISA (Chile).
